WEBVTT

00:00:00.850 --> 00:00:02.180
If you're so innocent,

00:00:02.180 --> 00:00:05.380
find us the real culprit, money and all.

00:00:05.380 --> 00:00:10.520
Three years ago, Natsumi embezzled money
from the organization.

00:00:10.520 --> 00:00:13.230
It says here the money
went to you, Mr. Kaieda.

00:00:13.230 --> 00:00:15.870
Sir, I'm sorry. I only took a couple million.

00:00:15.870 --> 00:00:20.220
But I know nothing of the missing billion.
I didn't kill Natsumi either!

00:00:26.430 --> 00:00:29.300
I've decided to trust you, Ichika.

00:00:29.300 --> 00:00:33.010
Let's both survive for our family's sake.

00:00:52.220 --> 00:00:56.410
[Ayumi Gido, Reboot - Day 3]

00:01:17.420 --> 00:01:21.510
Now don't misunderstand. This is just...

00:01:21.510 --> 00:01:25.770
Is she the reason you were avoiding me?

00:01:25.770 --> 00:01:26.820
No.

00:01:26.820 --> 00:01:29.870
Then why were you missing for half a year?

00:01:29.870 --> 00:01:31.970
Tell me what's going on.

00:01:38.490 --> 00:01:44.410
I was getting therapy.
Work got me depressed.

00:01:46.790 --> 00:01:51.370
We were celebrating my recovery.

00:01:52.270 --> 00:01:58.690
She just passed out after a few drinks.

00:01:58.690 --> 00:02:02.250
I saw her the other day, too.
Who is she?

00:02:02.250 --> 00:02:03.560
Someone I know from work.

00:02:03.560 --> 00:02:05.490
A fellow officer?

00:02:07.410 --> 00:02:08.800
An accountant.

00:02:08.800 --> 00:02:10.480
How do you know an accountant?

00:02:10.480 --> 00:02:12.240
I already told you.

00:02:13.020 --> 00:02:15.690
She's someone I met on the job.

00:02:15.690 --> 00:02:19.020
He's saying he wants you out.

00:02:20.890 --> 00:02:23.870
Why not accept the divorce already?

00:02:23.870 --> 00:02:26.850
I know he handed you the papers.

00:02:27.930 --> 00:02:30.950
I'm speaking to my husband right now.

00:02:30.950 --> 00:02:33.580
And you're interrupting our time together.

00:02:33.580 --> 00:02:35.450
Please leave us.

00:02:37.340 --> 00:02:39.830
You leave us.

00:02:48.680 --> 00:02:50.690
Sorry, could you...

00:03:05.850 --> 00:03:07.610
I'll be back.

00:03:14.100 --> 00:03:15.230
Well...

00:03:15.230 --> 00:03:16.940
Why didn't you chase her out?

00:03:16.940 --> 00:03:19.710
Well... I felt bad for her.

00:03:19.710 --> 00:03:22.650
You won't be fooling his wife, you know.

00:03:23.260 --> 00:03:26.850
That's why I was being so pushy.

00:03:29.840 --> 00:03:33.010
Cover up your bruises with this.

00:03:35.600 --> 00:03:39.970
W-What do I do now, Ichika?

00:03:42.070 --> 00:03:48.300
Anything you don't know, you "forgot about".

00:03:48.300 --> 00:03:51.980
Bring her somewhere to talk,
and end things quickly.

00:03:51.980 --> 00:03:55.600
I'll listen in, so keep me on the phone.

00:03:55.600 --> 00:03:57.000
Yes, ma'am.

00:03:57.000 --> 00:03:58.460
See you.

00:04:05.490 --> 00:04:07.970
Let's talk somewhere else.
My place is a mess.

00:04:13.120 --> 00:04:14.510
I'm getting changed.

00:04:14.510 --> 00:04:16.230
Be my guest.

00:04:33.980 --> 00:04:38.820
[Calling - I]

00:04:46.830 --> 00:04:48.400
Thanks.

00:04:52.990 --> 00:04:56.710
Mayu Gido, a nutritionist
at an elementary school.

00:04:56.710 --> 00:04:59.060
They met at 26, and then got married.

00:04:59.060 --> 00:05:02.820
They've been apart for 5 years,
and divorce is imminent for them.

00:05:02.820 --> 00:05:06.760
She's his wife, and I know nothing about her.

00:05:06.760 --> 00:05:09.030
How'd you get inside?

00:05:09.030 --> 00:05:11.180
I never gave you a key.

00:05:11.180 --> 00:05:13.080
I had the landlord let me in.

00:05:13.080 --> 00:05:15.680
I told them I was your wife.

00:05:23.180 --> 00:05:25.070
That burns!

00:05:28.690 --> 00:05:32.810
Mornings at a diner make me nostalgic.

00:05:32.810 --> 00:05:34.880
For?

00:05:34.880 --> 00:05:41.010
You proposed while downing a bowl of curry.

00:05:41.010 --> 00:05:43.040
Ah, their proposal.

00:05:45.550 --> 00:05:50.900
We promised to overcome
all difficulties together, remember?

00:05:50.900 --> 00:05:52.920
I forgot.

00:06:01.970 --> 00:06:04.860
Why didn't you come to me?

00:06:06.180 --> 00:06:10.980
You'd always respond to my texts,
and then suddenly, nothing.

00:06:10.980 --> 00:06:14.050
Do you realize how worried I was?

00:06:17.220 --> 00:06:22.110
You must have been spiraling
to take off a whole six months.

00:06:23.190 --> 00:06:27.370
I wish you'd told me.
I wanted to be there for you.

00:06:28.810 --> 00:06:33.370
Or is it that you loathe me now?

00:06:41.020 --> 00:06:43.160
[I: Don't pity her.]

00:06:48.830 --> 00:06:50.780
Let's end this.

00:06:51.420 --> 00:06:55.280
You're still young. You'll find someone else.

00:06:56.310 --> 00:06:57.990
I'm not leaving you.

00:06:59.160 --> 00:07:00.700
Please.

00:07:00.700 --> 00:07:03.730
Then why are you still wearing that necklace?

00:07:03.730 --> 00:07:05.930
I gave that to you.

00:07:05.930 --> 00:07:07.990
I forgot.

00:07:07.990 --> 00:07:11.320
Liar. You wouldn't forget.

00:07:11.320 --> 00:07:14.800
You flew out the house asking for a divorce

00:07:14.800 --> 00:07:18.980
without even explaining yourself.

00:07:20.030 --> 00:07:23.030
Tell me what's really going on.

00:07:24.410 --> 00:07:26.740
You're hiding something from me, aren't you?

00:07:30.290 --> 00:07:32.650
[I: Start wrapping up.]

00:07:37.350 --> 00:07:39.720
I gotta go. Duty calls.

00:07:39.720 --> 00:07:41.650
You've got a job too, no?

00:07:44.120 --> 00:07:46.340
[I: End this, now.]

00:07:49.410 --> 00:07:51.640
Don't come to my place again.

00:07:51.640 --> 00:07:54.040
I've had enough of you.

00:07:58.890 --> 00:08:02.200
I'm not filing the divorce
until you explain yourself.

00:08:09.730 --> 00:08:11.210
Leave it, I'll pay.

00:08:24.280 --> 00:08:27.360
I wrapped it up, Ichika.

00:08:28.120 --> 00:08:29.120
You were here?

00:08:29.120 --> 00:08:32.030
Yeah, I took a seat in the corner.

00:08:32.960 --> 00:08:33.850
Excuse me.

00:08:33.850 --> 00:08:34.900
Yes?

00:08:34.900 --> 00:08:36.820
Could we be put on the same bill?

00:08:36.820 --> 00:08:38.990
Of course.

00:08:41.680 --> 00:08:44.740
I think I'll get myself a mille crepe.

00:08:44.740 --> 00:08:46.160
And you?

00:08:46.160 --> 00:08:48.990
I feel awful. We're lying to her.

00:08:48.990 --> 00:08:53.310
How would she react
if she knew her husband was dead?

00:08:53.310 --> 00:08:57.980
Then will you do things over with her
in Gido's place?

00:08:57.980 --> 00:09:00.610
Of course not.

00:09:01.200 --> 00:09:05.170
You can't be giving her any false hope.

00:09:05.170 --> 00:09:07.980
But I can't just leave her.

00:09:09.750 --> 00:09:11.690
Oh? So she's your type.

00:09:11.690 --> 00:09:12.860
- No.
- She is a beauty.

00:09:12.860 --> 00:09:14.660
That's not what I meant.

00:09:14.660 --> 00:09:17.210
I feel bad for Natsumi.

00:09:20.010 --> 00:09:22.410
Natsumi is my one and only.

00:09:22.410 --> 00:09:25.170
I would never spare another woman a chance.

00:09:33.260 --> 00:09:35.360
She's long gone, though.

00:09:42.380 --> 00:09:47.250
You told me Gido and Mayu
were drifting apart.

00:09:47.250 --> 00:09:48.160
Yes.

00:09:48.160 --> 00:09:49.630
Was that another lie?

00:09:49.630 --> 00:09:51.140
No.

00:09:51.140 --> 00:09:53.960
That's the impression I got from Gido.

00:09:53.960 --> 00:09:56.390
What did Gido say about his wife?

00:09:57.050 --> 00:10:01.030
"I'm over her. I want her out of my life."

00:10:01.030 --> 00:10:03.240
But why?

00:10:03.240 --> 00:10:07.470
He said she was a pain to deal with.

00:10:07.470 --> 00:10:10.200
He wouldn't skimp on the insults, either.

00:10:10.200 --> 00:10:12.480
That's a bit much.

00:10:12.480 --> 00:10:17.010
But it seems like Mayu still cares for him.

00:10:19.590 --> 00:10:21.390
What do we do?

00:10:22.040 --> 00:10:24.040
You have to push her away.

00:10:24.040 --> 00:10:28.790
The worst thing you could do,
is lead her on.

00:10:31.300 --> 00:10:34.990
Besides, you have bigger problems
to deal with.

00:10:35.850 --> 00:10:38.590
If you don't find that money,
it's over for you.

00:10:39.790 --> 00:10:41.480
I know.

00:10:42.010 --> 00:10:43.670
I've brought your mille crepes.

00:10:43.670 --> 00:10:46.790
- Thank you.
- Here you go.

00:10:46.790 --> 00:10:48.640
Thank you.

00:10:57.210 --> 00:10:58.630
Your mask is slipping.

00:10:58.630 --> 00:11:01.760
Cut me some slack,
I want to enjoy this dessert.

00:11:32.180 --> 00:11:35.800
I'm sorry! I know nothing!

00:11:35.800 --> 00:11:38.670
I didn't steal no money!

00:11:39.780 --> 00:11:42.860
Machi told me all about you, Kaieda.

00:11:42.860 --> 00:11:45.920
She said you were a persistent fella.

00:11:45.920 --> 00:11:51.200
Hah! I'd never lay a hand on your girl.

00:11:54.990 --> 00:11:59.660
Our bond runs deeper than that.
Don't act like you know it all.

00:12:02.920 --> 00:12:06.070
Sorry, sorry. Forgive me.

00:12:06.070 --> 00:12:08.490
Please, forgive me!

00:12:08.490 --> 00:12:10.810
Mr. Kaieda, this is Goroku.

00:12:11.680 --> 00:12:13.410
[G]

00:12:13.410 --> 00:12:15.330
Sir, I'm innocent!

00:12:15.330 --> 00:12:19.990
It was Gido! He stole the money!
I was set up!

00:12:19.990 --> 00:12:24.000
But it's true you used Natsumi
to embezzle money, no?

00:12:26.340 --> 00:12:27.850
I'm sorry, sir.

00:12:27.850 --> 00:12:33.620
I'll pay it all back in triple -
no, quadruple!

00:12:33.620 --> 00:12:37.190
My company strives to make all parties happy,

00:12:37.190 --> 00:12:44.130
customers, staff,
and business partners alike.

00:12:44.130 --> 00:12:45.460
You are aware of those policies, yes?

00:12:45.460 --> 00:12:46.690
Yes, of course.

00:12:46.690 --> 00:12:51.420
Mr. Kaieda, you have worked tirelessly
for the betterment of my company.

00:12:51.420 --> 00:12:56.910
As such, I will give you one more chance.

00:12:56.910 --> 00:12:58.820
Thank you. Thank you, sir!

00:12:58.820 --> 00:13:01.390
I thank god, Buddha, and you, Mr. Goroku!

00:13:01.890 --> 00:13:06.200
However, if you're so innocent...

00:13:07.370 --> 00:13:12.020
Find us the real culprit by midnight.

00:13:12.020 --> 00:13:13.170
Sir, it's Gido.

00:13:13.170 --> 00:13:16.280
Then find me the proof.

00:13:16.280 --> 00:13:21.440
If Gido's guilty, he'll put the blame on you.

00:13:21.440 --> 00:13:24.730
At this point, it's either you or him.

00:13:24.730 --> 00:13:30.750
And I only want to keep capable folk around.

00:13:30.750 --> 00:13:34.690
I hope I can expect great things from you.

00:13:34.690 --> 00:13:37.790
Yes, sir. I will not let you down.

00:13:40.050 --> 00:13:41.430
- Come on in.
- Excuse me.

00:13:42.270 --> 00:13:43.440
Sir, Mr. Kobayashi's here.

00:13:43.440 --> 00:13:46.780
- Hello.
- Mr. Kobayashi! Thank you for coming.

00:13:46.780 --> 00:13:47.750
Nice to see you, Mr. Goroku.

00:13:47.750 --> 00:13:48.810
Likewise.

00:13:48.810 --> 00:13:52.200
Hey, good for you, Mr. Kaieda.

00:13:52.200 --> 00:13:55.640
You've still got a bit left in you.

00:13:56.670 --> 00:14:00.680
Fuyuhashi, I want you to lend me one.

00:14:01.780 --> 00:14:03.480
A gun.

00:14:04.510 --> 00:14:07.000
Anything's fair game now, right?

00:14:13.720 --> 00:14:16.000
The times wouldn't agree with you, sir.

00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:17.180
N-Now hold on...

00:14:17.180 --> 00:14:21.520
We gotta tread carefully nowadays.

00:14:24.950 --> 00:14:28.980
I can't just let you go on a rampage.

00:14:28.980 --> 00:14:31.580
You think you know any better, brat?

00:14:31.580 --> 00:14:35.320
I've been working with my noggin all my life!

00:14:43.440 --> 00:14:47.180
Don't go giving Mr. Goroku
or the organization any trouble.

00:14:47.180 --> 00:14:50.910
And be careful how you handle it.

00:14:50.910 --> 00:14:53.200
Kiriya. Give him the rundown.

00:14:53.200 --> 00:14:54.980
Yes, sir.

00:14:54.980 --> 00:14:57.240
Least I know how to handle my women.

00:14:57.240 --> 00:14:59.440
Another word, and you're dead.

00:15:00.540 --> 00:15:02.470
Learn to take a joke, kid.

00:15:02.470 --> 00:15:05.140
Okay. First, this is the safety catch.

00:15:05.140 --> 00:15:09.400
Press it down, and you'll get your bullets.

00:15:09.400 --> 00:15:11.120
- Excellent.
- Hey, watch it!

00:15:11.120 --> 00:15:13.860
- Bang!
- No pointing it at me!

00:15:19.960 --> 00:15:21.140
Morning.

00:15:21.140 --> 00:15:22.930
- Sir.
- Morning.

00:15:22.930 --> 00:15:25.620
Adachi, thanks for your help yesterday.

00:15:25.620 --> 00:15:27.870
Anytime. But sir...

00:15:27.870 --> 00:15:30.230
There you are, Gido. She's waiting for you.

00:15:30.230 --> 00:15:33.000
Get on in already.

00:15:37.710 --> 00:15:42.160
I came to give Mr. Mikami my regards.
You took a long break, after all.

00:15:42.160 --> 00:15:44.890
I hadn't seen her since the wedding.

00:15:44.890 --> 00:15:48.690
I heard this beauty nursed you, you lucky dog.

00:15:48.690 --> 00:15:49.940
Don't take that for granted.

00:15:49.940 --> 00:15:51.670
Mine's already getting round.

00:15:51.670 --> 00:15:55.030
Sir, no speaking about body image like that.

00:15:55.030 --> 00:15:56.440
Even about my own wife?

00:15:56.440 --> 00:16:00.580
Just don't push yourself, dear.

00:16:04.050 --> 00:16:06.400
Thank you for looking after my husband.

00:16:06.400 --> 00:16:07.510
Of course.

00:16:07.510 --> 00:16:10.620
Ma'am, I'm learning much from Inspector Gido

00:16:10.620 --> 00:16:12.970
as I'm still a newcomer here.

00:16:12.970 --> 00:16:15.700
Still, I will do all that I can
to support your husband.

00:16:15.700 --> 00:16:17.770
Thank you.

00:16:17.770 --> 00:16:19.050
Then I shall get going.

00:16:19.050 --> 00:16:20.410
Thanks again for visiting.

00:16:31.110 --> 00:16:33.690
This is just a little something for you all.

00:16:33.690 --> 00:16:37.440
Thank you all for taking care of Gido.

00:16:38.600 --> 00:16:39.910
We both appreciate it.

00:16:39.910 --> 00:16:42.840
I'm glad it seems you two are getting along.

00:16:42.840 --> 00:16:44.110
What?

00:16:44.110 --> 00:16:48.780
I remember you were going to file for a divorce.

00:16:48.780 --> 00:16:52.740
Seems like depression restored your love, eh?

00:16:52.740 --> 00:16:55.090
Sir, what did you and Mayu talk about?

00:16:55.090 --> 00:16:59.030
We were chatting about your attitude
at the office.

00:16:59.030 --> 00:17:02.700
She wanted to know what you were up to
before your leave as well.

00:17:02.700 --> 00:17:04.810
Seems like she's really worried about you.

00:17:04.810 --> 00:17:08.180
You've scored a great wife, Gido.

00:17:08.180 --> 00:17:10.420
Treat her right, yeah?

00:17:12.970 --> 00:17:15.710
Sir, shall we debrief?

00:17:15.710 --> 00:17:17.450
Hold that thought.

00:17:18.200 --> 00:17:20.690
I guess he's seeing his wife off.

00:17:20.690 --> 00:17:22.150
Now that's love.

00:17:22.150 --> 00:17:25.170
Seems uncharacteristic of Mr. Gido, though.

00:17:34.790 --> 00:17:36.310
Ichika, bad news.

00:17:36.310 --> 00:17:39.530
One moment, please.

00:17:47.500 --> 00:17:49.060
What's wrong?

00:17:49.060 --> 00:17:51.080
Mayu came to the office.

00:17:51.080 --> 00:17:52.400
What? Why?

00:17:52.400 --> 00:17:56.620
I don't know. She came to give her regards?

00:17:56.620 --> 00:17:58.680
Why would she do that?

00:18:00.140 --> 00:18:02.860
She's either extremely hung up on Gido,

00:18:02.860 --> 00:18:06.150
or she's a bonafide stalker.

00:18:06.150 --> 00:18:10.610
I really can't be dealing with a stalker now.

00:18:12.980 --> 00:18:15.000
Sorry, I'll talk with you later.

00:18:16.030 --> 00:18:17.570
Morning, Mr. Gido.

00:18:17.570 --> 00:18:19.960
Morning, Inspector Makita.

00:18:19.960 --> 00:18:22.780
Quite the secluded place
to be taking a call, no?

00:18:23.750 --> 00:18:26.800
I wanted some private time with the wife.

00:18:28.830 --> 00:18:35.680
Cherishing those that are close, eh?
How sentimental.

00:18:35.680 --> 00:18:38.610
I think relationships like his
are rather lovely, sir.

00:18:39.570 --> 00:18:43.140
Personally, my career is at a halt
because of my wife.

00:18:43.140 --> 00:18:45.570
You've heard of the hit-and-run, I take it.

00:18:45.570 --> 00:18:50.680
Though I suppose it's brought us
closer together, in a way.

00:18:51.550 --> 00:18:55.340
That frankness of yours
is very uncharacteristic of an inspector.

00:18:55.340 --> 00:18:57.580
I get that often.

00:18:57.580 --> 00:19:01.120
Secrets are just not my thing.

00:19:01.120 --> 00:19:06.070
Right, introductions. This is Yuuri Hijikata,
from the Second Investigation Team.

00:19:07.360 --> 00:19:08.850
Pleasure meeting you.

00:19:08.850 --> 00:19:10.940
The TMPD's Second Investigation Team.

00:19:10.940 --> 00:19:15.820
They specialize in investigating scams
and other malpractices.

00:19:15.820 --> 00:19:18.300
The name's Ayumi Gido,
First Investigation Team.

00:19:20.990 --> 00:19:22.860
Did you need something from me?

00:19:23.440 --> 00:19:27.350
I hear you have ties with Kou Fuyuhashi.

00:19:27.350 --> 00:19:33.930
That's correct. I currently use him as my S.

00:19:33.930 --> 00:19:36.660
He is your informant? I see.

00:19:37.880 --> 00:19:45.310
We believe Fuyuhashi is hiring part-timers
for shady business with his street kids.

00:19:45.310 --> 00:19:49.010
Banking fraud, eh?
I'll leave that case to your team.

00:19:49.010 --> 00:19:52.800
Our team focuses on murders and all that.

00:19:52.800 --> 00:19:58.230
We believe a bigger organization
is backing Fuyuhashi's team.

00:19:59.530 --> 00:20:02.410
Are you aware of the GooSix Corporation?

00:20:03.860 --> 00:20:09.010
The folks who deal with restaurants
and hotels, as I recall?

00:20:09.010 --> 00:20:14.690
Yes. Fuyuhashi has been seen visiting
associate companies of GooSix.

00:20:14.690 --> 00:20:22.320
Rumor has it he has his part-timers
create corporate bank accounts as well.

00:20:22.320 --> 00:20:24.200
And what of it?

00:20:24.710 --> 00:20:27.370
Though this is only a speculation,

00:20:27.370 --> 00:20:32.420
we believe GooSix's CEO
is using Fuyuhashi's group

00:20:32.420 --> 00:20:37.090
to organize an extensive
money laundering scheme.

00:20:37.090 --> 00:20:40.800
So the police have their suspicions
about Goroku.

00:20:41.460 --> 00:20:47.000
If you know of anything between Fuyuhashi
and the GooSix Corp.,

00:20:47.000 --> 00:20:50.070
we would appreciate the intel you have.

00:20:52.440 --> 00:20:56.030
Unfortunately I've heard nothing of it.

00:20:57.930 --> 00:21:01.810
I see. Then I shall visit again
if I have any further questions.

00:21:01.810 --> 00:21:04.900
You're welcome any time.

00:21:13.990 --> 00:21:19.370
If they catch on to Goroku's schemes,
Gido won't get off lightly.

00:21:19.370 --> 00:21:23.790
Do I tell Goroku the police suspect him?

00:21:23.790 --> 00:21:26.000
Your thoughts, Inspector?

00:21:26.540 --> 00:21:32.880
I believe your suspicions are correct.
He was likely bought out by Fuyuhashi.

00:21:32.880 --> 00:21:37.320
Wataru Goroku is an influential man.
He even has a hand in politics.

00:21:37.320 --> 00:21:41.220
I suspect Goroku is Gido's true master.

00:21:41.220 --> 00:21:47.520
If that's so, we may have landed ourselves
an even bigger catch.

00:21:52.400 --> 00:21:55.250
[First Members Office Building
of the House of Representatives]

00:21:55.250 --> 00:21:57.470
I hear the prime minister's made his call.

00:21:57.470 --> 00:21:59.440
He's self destructing.

00:21:59.440 --> 00:22:02.120
If elections run now, our party's done for.

00:22:02.120 --> 00:22:04.310
Another party might take the spot.

00:22:04.310 --> 00:22:06.910
Contact our supporters as soon as possible.

00:22:06.910 --> 00:22:09.050
They say elections are coming up.

00:22:17.740 --> 00:22:19.450
Pardon me, sir.

00:22:19.450 --> 00:22:23.950
[Yaichi Makita]

00:22:24.950 --> 00:22:28.180
We've looked more into
Natsumi Hayase's background.

00:22:28.180 --> 00:22:33.310
Natsumi was raised by her single mother.

00:22:33.310 --> 00:22:36.240
In high school,
her mother passed away in an accident,

00:22:36.240 --> 00:22:40.090
and she attended college on scholarship,
while majoring in accounting.

00:22:40.090 --> 00:22:43.530
She worked at an accounting firm
to pay back her scholarship after graduating,

00:22:43.530 --> 00:22:47.010
while studying to become
a certified accountant.

00:22:47.010 --> 00:22:50.210
This was when she met Riku Hayase,
and eventually married him.

00:22:54.610 --> 00:22:55.730
Could I get one of this, please?

00:22:55.730 --> 00:22:57.660
Of course.

00:22:58.500 --> 00:22:59.680
Here you go.

00:22:59.680 --> 00:23:01.020
Thank you.

00:23:02.990 --> 00:23:07.080
Frequent chance encounters
brought them together at cafes,

00:23:07.080 --> 00:23:09.860
and they eventually began
rounding them together.

00:23:19.070 --> 00:23:20.550
- I understand completely.
- Hm?

00:23:20.550 --> 00:23:24.440
Cakes are best enjoyed
when starting with the fruit on top.

00:23:24.440 --> 00:23:26.750
Starting with the tart fruit...

00:23:26.750 --> 00:23:29.500
Makes cake taste all the sweeter.

00:23:33.890 --> 00:23:38.770
With her husband's support,
Natsumi soon became a certified accountant.

00:23:38.770 --> 00:23:41.940
They were a well-known couple
in their neighborhood.

00:23:41.940 --> 00:23:45.470
I know that better than anyone.

00:23:45.470 --> 00:23:48.030
That's nothing new though, is it?

00:23:48.030 --> 00:23:51.600
No, sir. Here's where it gets interesting.

00:23:51.600 --> 00:23:53.860
We found another side to her.

00:23:55.720 --> 00:24:02.150
According to a friend from college,
Natsumi worked the nightlife as a student.

00:24:02.150 --> 00:24:07.360
Though she worked with several companies
after becoming certified,

00:24:07.360 --> 00:24:14.410
she also helped a man named "Kou Fuyuhashi"
start up an NPO.

00:24:14.410 --> 00:24:20.970
He is an individual whom Team Two
currently has their eyes on.

00:24:22.990 --> 00:24:25.340
Inspector Gido.

00:24:25.340 --> 00:24:28.670
If I'm not mistaken,

00:24:28.670 --> 00:24:33.020
you met up with this man
by the Hayase Patisserie, no?

00:24:37.480 --> 00:24:41.050
Fuyuhashi's my informant.

00:24:41.050 --> 00:24:43.390
You get connections like that
in this line of work.

00:24:44.210 --> 00:24:45.950
Is that so.

00:24:45.950 --> 00:24:48.690
I apologize for questioning you, sir.

00:24:49.400 --> 00:24:50.910
Any leads on Riku Hayase?

00:24:50.910 --> 00:24:54.060
We had a citizen report a sighting.

00:24:54.060 --> 00:24:55.310
A sighting?

00:24:55.310 --> 00:25:01.070
A transportation company claims
their live-in worker looks just like him.

00:25:01.070 --> 00:25:04.550
This is the first "sighting"
that's been reported in a while.

00:25:04.550 --> 00:25:06.950
I'm sure it's another false lead.

00:25:06.950 --> 00:25:07.990
I'll go check regardless.

00:25:07.990 --> 00:25:09.280
I'll leave that to you.

00:25:09.280 --> 00:25:10.740
You're not coming along, sir?

00:25:10.740 --> 00:25:13.630
I'm going to speak with the folks
at Hayase Patisserie.

00:25:13.630 --> 00:25:15.240
Again?

00:25:15.240 --> 00:25:19.340
Gaining their trust
will make the investigation easier.

00:25:19.340 --> 00:25:23.510
I'll handle every matter
regarding that family, got that?

00:25:23.510 --> 00:25:24.980
Yes, sir.

00:25:26.960 --> 00:25:28.860
One more thing, Inspector.

00:25:28.860 --> 00:25:32.280
Here's that spare key to your locker.

00:25:32.280 --> 00:25:33.560
It was delivered earlier.

00:25:33.560 --> 00:25:35.580
Thanks, I appreciate it.

00:25:38.690 --> 00:25:44.300
The more I look into Natsumi,
the more I learn of her.

00:25:45.030 --> 00:25:47.990
Should I really be digging this deep
into her past?

00:26:07.360 --> 00:26:10.480
I thought he was pushing for a divorce.

00:26:10.480 --> 00:26:13.010
He still keeps this necklace on, too.

00:26:13.010 --> 00:26:15.320
What exactly is going on here?

00:26:47.040 --> 00:26:50.220
There wasn't a laptop at Gido's place.

00:26:50.220 --> 00:26:55.370
There might be something
related to the case in here.

00:27:13.720 --> 00:27:15.860
Hello.

00:27:15.860 --> 00:27:17.550
Welcome home, Ta...

00:27:22.860 --> 00:27:24.730
Takumi.

00:27:24.730 --> 00:27:28.050
- Could I get a cream puff?
- Sure.

00:27:28.050 --> 00:27:32.040
Grandma and I made more improvements.

00:27:42.040 --> 00:27:46.750
Wash your hands.
You're serving a customer, remember?

00:27:46.750 --> 00:27:48.700
Sorry, sir.

00:27:59.790 --> 00:28:01.770
I'll take it as is.

00:28:03.200 --> 00:28:05.490
Thanks again.

00:28:23.840 --> 00:28:25.820
How is it?

00:28:25.820 --> 00:28:27.740
Tastes delicious.

00:28:27.740 --> 00:28:29.340
Right?

00:28:30.960 --> 00:28:33.850
Customers will like that.

00:28:36.890 --> 00:28:38.430
What's up?

00:28:38.980 --> 00:28:41.420
Grandma's pushing herself.

00:28:41.420 --> 00:28:44.410
Her arms and hips are hurting.

00:28:46.190 --> 00:28:49.620
If I knew what I was doing,
I could make them instead.

00:28:49.620 --> 00:28:51.990
But I still suck at it.

00:28:53.070 --> 00:28:55.940
I should have had Dad teach me.

00:29:19.250 --> 00:29:21.750
This is my number.

00:29:21.750 --> 00:29:26.720
Call me about anything,
be it home or school.

00:29:26.720 --> 00:29:29.070
I'll be there to listen, alright?

00:29:29.070 --> 00:29:30.460
Thanks.

00:29:30.460 --> 00:29:33.090
I could give you cake-making tips, too.

00:29:33.090 --> 00:29:36.870
Baking's a hobby of mine, remember?

00:29:36.870 --> 00:29:39.540
I'd say I've got the skills.

00:29:39.540 --> 00:29:42.040
You'd never beat my dad, though.

00:29:43.820 --> 00:29:46.920
Taku? Is that you?

00:29:46.920 --> 00:29:47.890
Hi, Grandma.

00:29:47.890 --> 00:29:49.830
Welcome home, dear.

00:29:50.990 --> 00:29:52.310
Oh, Mr. Gido.

00:29:52.310 --> 00:29:56.260
Ma'am, your cream puffs have improved.

00:29:56.260 --> 00:29:58.600
Thank you.

00:29:58.600 --> 00:30:01.960
But my, your timing is impeccable.
Your wife is visiting.

00:30:02.820 --> 00:30:04.070
Pardon?

00:30:04.070 --> 00:30:08.010
She came to offer a prayer.
What a wonderful lass indeed.

00:30:13.680 --> 00:30:16.980
Mayu, your husband is here.

00:30:19.270 --> 00:30:21.340
Would you also like to stay for tea?

00:30:21.340 --> 00:30:23.690
No, thank you. Come on, let's go.

00:30:23.690 --> 00:30:25.330
You don't need to be so pushy.

00:30:25.330 --> 00:30:28.380
I apologize for the trouble my wife caused.

00:30:28.380 --> 00:30:31.720
Oh, she was no trouble.

00:30:31.720 --> 00:30:33.710
Mayu, you're welcome again any time.

00:30:33.710 --> 00:30:35.790
Thank you.

00:30:42.530 --> 00:30:44.630
Why are you here?

00:30:45.930 --> 00:30:48.070
I saw you had a box from this patisserie.

00:30:48.070 --> 00:30:49.300
[Hayase Patisserie]

00:30:49.300 --> 00:30:52.640
But you don't have a sweet tooth.

00:30:55.620 --> 00:30:59.080
As it turns out, you're looking into a case
involving this store.

00:30:59.080 --> 00:31:00.730
Unbelievable.

00:31:00.730 --> 00:31:04.610
You're treading into an investigation.

00:31:08.510 --> 00:31:10.930
I want to know more about you.

00:31:11.970 --> 00:31:14.140
Don't ever come here again.

00:31:14.140 --> 00:31:16.180
And don't even think about following me around.

00:31:17.760 --> 00:31:21.420
I won't be leaving you.

00:31:30.340 --> 00:31:32.380
What is up with that woman?

00:31:32.380 --> 00:31:34.990
This is insane.

00:31:44.420 --> 00:31:45.650
Gido, speaking.

00:31:45.650 --> 00:31:47.250
It's me.

00:31:49.200 --> 00:31:51.090
Kaieda.

00:31:51.090 --> 00:31:53.910
Bingo! I'm still kicking, bucko.

00:31:53.910 --> 00:31:57.310
If anything, I'm more invigorated than ever.

00:31:57.310 --> 00:32:00.800
So, where's the one billion, Gido?

00:32:00.800 --> 00:32:02.780
I'd really appreciate your cooperation here.

00:32:02.780 --> 00:32:05.520
If I don't show results today,
I can kiss my life goodbye.

00:32:05.520 --> 00:32:07.820
Sorry, but I've got no time to cooperate.

00:32:07.820 --> 00:32:10.030
Find a way out of this mess yourself.

00:32:10.030 --> 00:32:13.090
You sure about talking like that, Gido?

00:32:13.090 --> 00:32:16.420
Don't blame me
if your special someone pays the price.

00:32:19.890 --> 00:32:22.050
I think she was wearing blue?

00:32:23.610 --> 00:32:26.280
She's a real beauty, I'll give you that.

00:32:26.280 --> 00:32:28.840
Your wife's name was Mayu, was it?

00:32:30.990 --> 00:32:33.400
She's walking past a park right now.

00:32:33.400 --> 00:32:35.200
No one's around, either.

00:32:35.200 --> 00:32:38.560
Sounds mighty dangerous.
You oughta protect her.

00:32:38.560 --> 00:32:41.920
Kaieda. Kaieda, wait.

00:33:00.890 --> 00:33:02.440
Mayu.

00:33:07.010 --> 00:33:08.470
Mayu!

00:33:10.320 --> 00:33:11.910
Mayu!

00:33:14.350 --> 00:33:17.060
No need to shout.

00:33:19.770 --> 00:33:21.790
What did you do with Mayu?

00:33:23.790 --> 00:33:26.470
I'm having an expert tail her.

00:33:26.470 --> 00:33:29.780
One of my old clients
had connections, you could say.

00:33:29.780 --> 00:33:33.380
I can make her disappear,
whenever, wherever.

00:33:35.250 --> 00:33:37.160
Easy there.

00:33:37.160 --> 00:33:40.170
If I don't check in every 30 minutes,

00:33:40.170 --> 00:33:42.750
she's to be killed, no questions asked.

00:33:42.750 --> 00:33:45.550
So keep your hands to yourself.

00:33:46.600 --> 00:33:48.600
Where's the billion yen?

00:33:49.240 --> 00:33:50.620
I don't know.

00:33:50.620 --> 00:33:53.810
You think that'd work on me?

00:33:54.490 --> 00:33:55.370
I forgot.

00:33:55.370 --> 00:33:58.180
I'm not buying it.

00:33:58.180 --> 00:34:05.210
We planned to steal that billion
with Natsumi three years ago.

00:34:06.570 --> 00:34:08.270
That's when it happened.

00:34:09.960 --> 00:34:16.490
Someone took the cash before we could,
and Natsumi disappeared.

00:34:16.490 --> 00:34:19.490
Natsumi Hayase has disappeared.

00:34:20.400 --> 00:34:25.050
She may be the one who stole our billion yen.

00:34:25.050 --> 00:34:28.600
Everyone assumed Natsumi ran off
with the money.

00:34:28.600 --> 00:34:30.870
But then her remains turned up.

00:34:30.870 --> 00:34:33.750
Which means someone killed her.

00:34:34.540 --> 00:34:39.260
The culprit's either you, or me.

00:34:39.260 --> 00:34:43.820
And since I did nothing, you're guilty.

00:34:43.820 --> 00:34:45.790
So where's the money?

00:34:45.790 --> 00:34:47.680
Still got nothing for me?

00:34:47.680 --> 00:34:49.520
Did Gido do it?

00:34:49.520 --> 00:34:52.010
Did he threaten Natsumi,
and steal the money?

00:34:52.010 --> 00:34:55.470
I don't mind killing your wife right now.

00:34:55.470 --> 00:34:57.610
Mayu and I are through.

00:34:57.610 --> 00:35:00.030
Who cares what happens to her.

00:35:00.820 --> 00:35:03.150
Then I'll give the order now. Hey -

00:35:03.150 --> 00:35:04.850
Fine!

00:35:06.420 --> 00:35:07.960
I'll get you the money.

00:35:07.960 --> 00:35:11.010
I knew you had it, scumbag.

00:35:11.010 --> 00:35:12.850
Your deadline's 9PM tonight.

00:35:12.850 --> 00:35:15.780
Bring it all to the container port.

00:35:15.780 --> 00:35:18.100
If you're late, your wife's dead.

00:35:18.100 --> 00:35:19.770
Alright.

00:35:22.170 --> 00:35:26.030
Gido had plans to steal the money?
He never told me.

00:35:26.030 --> 00:35:27.880
Really?

00:35:27.880 --> 00:35:30.790
You said you would trust me.

00:35:32.350 --> 00:35:35.960
Right, sorry. I'm a bit scared, is all.

00:35:43.060 --> 00:35:48.450
What do I do if Gido murdered Natsumi?

00:35:48.450 --> 00:35:50.300
Want to stop here?

00:35:55.380 --> 00:35:57.860
No, let's press on. For Natsumi's sake.

00:36:08.250 --> 00:36:10.730
Is that his fingerprint you took?

00:36:21.120 --> 00:36:24.840
Let's check his emails
from around when Natsumi died.

00:36:31.540 --> 00:36:32.810
[Warehouse Rental]

00:36:32.810 --> 00:36:34.740
A warehouse?

00:36:35.610 --> 00:36:39.920
He rented it out right before Natsumi passed.

00:36:44.790 --> 00:36:46.210
Thank you, really.

00:36:46.210 --> 00:36:50.050
You will be charged next month
for the new key.

00:36:50.050 --> 00:36:54.790
We'll make a spare using this one,
so please return it to the desk afterwards.

00:36:54.790 --> 00:36:57.090
You will receive your new key in two weeks.

00:36:57.090 --> 00:36:58.920
Thank you.

00:37:00.180 --> 00:37:01.620
This one.

00:37:55.240 --> 00:37:56.630
What did you find?

00:37:57.830 --> 00:38:02.070
[Natsumi Hayase]

00:38:04.460 --> 00:38:07.010
Gido, he really did...

00:38:14.530 --> 00:38:16.520
I'll go to the police and confess everything.

00:38:16.520 --> 00:38:20.190
No. You don't have enough evidence.

00:38:20.990 --> 00:38:25.190
Our first priority is rescuing Mayu.

00:38:58.510 --> 00:39:00.640
Give me your car keys.

00:39:03.750 --> 00:39:05.330
Kneel.

00:39:07.850 --> 00:39:09.830
Hands behind your head.

00:39:11.790 --> 00:39:13.740
Don't you dare move, you hear?

00:39:24.340 --> 00:39:25.890
W-What's going on?

00:39:25.890 --> 00:39:26.740
[G]

00:39:26.740 --> 00:39:29.590
Evening, Mr. Kaieda. This is Goroku.

00:39:30.730 --> 00:39:33.890
Kidnapping a civilian was a risky move.

00:39:33.890 --> 00:39:37.290
I cannot allow your actions to slide.

00:39:37.290 --> 00:39:41.230
I had the folks tailing Mrs. Mayu back down.

00:39:41.230 --> 00:39:44.510
But sir, this was all to retrieve the money.

00:39:44.510 --> 00:39:47.740
Gido has the billion, I'm sure of it!

00:39:47.740 --> 00:39:50.270
We've already found the money, Mr. Kaieda.

00:39:50.270 --> 00:39:51.270
What?

00:39:51.270 --> 00:39:54.080
In one of your many apartments, in fact.

00:39:54.880 --> 00:39:59.210
A girl you brought home gave us the tip.

00:40:00.290 --> 00:40:02.380
That's impossible.

00:40:03.600 --> 00:40:07.020
You. You set me up!

00:40:08.180 --> 00:40:10.040
Mr. Kaieda.

00:40:12.220 --> 00:40:15.050
Let's drop the act, why don't we?

00:40:15.050 --> 00:40:17.080
Traitor!

00:40:19.540 --> 00:40:24.980
He's the one who killed Natsumi
and stole the money.

00:40:24.980 --> 00:40:27.530
You killed her!

00:40:32.090 --> 00:40:34.410
Sir, I'm handing the phone to Gido.

00:40:35.850 --> 00:40:39.320
Sorry to doubt you, Gido.

00:40:39.320 --> 00:40:41.790
I'm just glad my suspicions were cleared.

00:40:41.790 --> 00:40:45.120
Here's to our continued partnership.

00:40:45.120 --> 00:40:46.890
Likewise.

00:40:47.580 --> 00:40:50.950
Let me know if the police
start making their move.

00:40:50.950 --> 00:40:56.690
Betray me, and you'll meet a fate
similar to Kaieda's.

00:41:02.260 --> 00:41:03.720
What're you going to do with him?

00:41:03.720 --> 00:41:06.500
Isn't that obvious? We're getting rid him.

00:41:06.500 --> 00:41:10.780
The hole's gonna be a hassle to dig though.

00:41:15.620 --> 00:41:20.300
You really had no hand in Natsumi's death?

00:41:20.300 --> 00:41:22.430
You're getting on my nerves, punk.

00:41:24.130 --> 00:41:26.000
Is that so.

00:41:26.960 --> 00:41:33.980
Natsumi must be glad the culprit was caught.

00:41:59.430 --> 00:42:00.730
Thank you.

00:42:00.730 --> 00:42:02.290
Whatever.

00:42:02.290 --> 00:42:05.110
I just wanted that old fart gone already.

00:42:10.320 --> 00:42:11.540
This stays between us.

00:42:11.540 --> 00:42:16.190
We know. Don't even bother telling us
what really happened.

00:42:26.880 --> 00:42:32.280
So long as we can live in peace,
I don't care about the truth.

00:42:52.130 --> 00:42:59.240
I've rebooted as the man
who murdered my wife.

00:43:01.030 --> 00:43:04.780
We won't know
unless we find whoever killed Gido.

00:43:04.780 --> 00:43:07.820
I'm not blaming you, Ichika.

00:43:08.390 --> 00:43:13.060
I just feel like an absolute fool.

00:43:15.670 --> 00:43:21.350
Natsumi was suffering on her own.

00:43:21.350 --> 00:43:24.040
She had so many secrets to her.

00:43:28.370 --> 00:43:31.030
If I had ever noticed...

00:43:32.340 --> 00:43:35.380
Things wouldn't have turned out this way.

00:43:41.590 --> 00:43:43.240
If you'll excuse me.

00:43:56.200 --> 00:43:57.890
Welcome home.

00:44:01.790 --> 00:44:04.220
I told you not to drop by again.

00:44:06.760 --> 00:44:08.150
I won't be leaving you.

00:44:08.150 --> 00:44:10.240
Enough.

00:44:12.670 --> 00:44:15.820
You aren't my wife.

00:44:15.820 --> 00:44:18.490
Don't show yourself to me again.

00:44:18.490 --> 00:44:21.910
I know you're not my husband.

00:44:24.550 --> 00:44:27.010
I had my suspicions from the start.

00:44:28.500 --> 00:44:32.380
But hugging you confirmed it.
You aren't Gido.

00:44:35.480 --> 00:44:36.880
What are you talking about?

00:44:36.880 --> 00:44:39.790
Gido was investigating a certain man.

00:44:39.790 --> 00:44:44.600
And you're desperate to protect
that man's family.

00:44:46.600 --> 00:44:51.050
You are Riku Hayase, are you not?

00:44:54.600 --> 00:44:56.440
I promise I won't tell a soul.

00:44:56.440 --> 00:44:57.980
I promise, so please.

00:44:57.980 --> 00:45:00.550
I just want to see Gido again.

00:45:00.550 --> 00:45:02.280
Please, tell me where he is.

00:45:02.280 --> 00:45:05.950
You're not making any sense. Leave.

00:45:06.730 --> 00:45:09.220
Gido called me today.

00:45:12.540 --> 00:45:13.620
Today?

00:45:13.620 --> 00:45:17.930
He warned me, and said I was being tailed.

00:45:17.930 --> 00:45:20.000
But that wasn't "you".

00:45:21.880 --> 00:45:24.000
That was the real Gido.

00:45:28.580 --> 00:45:33.740
Gido... is still alive?

00:45:38.640 --> 00:45:40.330
Where is Gido?
